This is a luarock of the "posix" part of


Lrexlib 2.6
===========

|  by Reuben Thomas (rrt@sc3d.org)
|  and Shmuel Zeigerman (shmuz@013net.net) [maintainer]


using some autoconf-stuff from


                               luaposix
                               --------

                     Reuben Thomas <rrt@sc3d.org>
                http://luaforge.net/projects/luaposix


Thanx a million!

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The easiest way to install it should be(come):

  luarocks install regex

but for some time a

  luarocks --from=https://github.com/downloads/Themroc/regex install regex

(which installs the latest development version) might work better...


If you want (or have to) use the GBS (a.k.a. "auto-tools"), a commandline like

./autogen.sh; CPPFLAGS=-I/usr/include/lua5.1 ./configure

should prepare it. Then, these special targets can be used:

make dev-dist	# create a .tar.xz file w/o that big fat autogenerated
		# stuff. Instead, autogen.sh will be included

make rockspec	# create a .rockspec file plus a .tar.gz file like above

make src-rock	# pack the .rockspec and the .tar.gz in a zip archive with
		# .rock as extension

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The manual:

  http://rrthomas.github.com/lrexlib/manual.html

Just replace 'rex.' by 'regex.', 'rex_posix' by 'regex' and ignore the PCRE,
GNU, Oniguruma and TRE sections.
